## Coding conventions

- Async-first. All HA setup methods async.
- `_LOGGER = logging.getLogger(__name__)` then `_LOGGER.debug/info/warning/error/exception`. Never `print`.
- Type hints on every public function and class.
- `@callback` decorator for sync handlers passed to HA.
- No bare `except:` â€” specify exception classes (`aiohttp.ClientError`, `asyncio.TimeoutError`, vendor classes).
- No blocking I/O in event loop. HTTP via `homeassistant.helpers.aiohttp_client.async_get_clientsession(hass)`.
- DataUpdateCoordinator pattern for polling integrations.
- Validate config entry data with `voluptuous` on setup.
- Constants in `const.py`. No magic numbers in business logic.

## Review guidelines

For Codex GitHub App + on-demand Claude Code Action reviewers.

P0 (block merge):
- Secrets, credentials, tokens in code, comments, or logs
- Blocking I/O in async event loop (`requests.`, `time.sleep`, sync file ops)
- Removal of error handling on external API calls
- Removal of `voluptuous` schema validation on config entry data
- Hardcoded HA URLs, ports, or user identifiers

P1 (strong fix before merge):
- Missing tests on new public functions, entities, or coordinator methods
- Bare `except:` / `except Exception:` without `_LOGGER.exception` or explicit re-raise
- `# type: ignore` without a `# reason:` comment
- `print()` in committed code
- Direct API calls outside the coordinator
- Public API change without README / manifest.json update

P2 (nit):
- Naming inconsistencies vs HA conventions (`async_setup_entry`, `_async_update_data`)
- Dead imports
- Style drift from this AGENTS.md

